    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Crankcase, Crankshaft, and Camshaft -
        Removal - Coolant Heater (if equipped)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Coolant Heater (if equipped)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure coolant has been drained out of the engine or at least drained to a level below
                the coolant heater, if simply servicing the heater.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen 5/32 in hex socket head cap screw sufficient to remove the coolant heater from the
                crankcase.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean out coolant heater cavity at crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
